                "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
              },
            ],
          },
          "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "<p><small>9:12pm PST</small> - Technical Summary:On February 20th from 2:34PM PST, we began receiving reports from customers who were seeing a “For some reason, Slack couldn’t load” error when attempting to access Slack. By 7:34PM PST, we determined that everything was working as expected and all affected customers have been followed up directly for further investigation.</p><p><small>7:44pm PST</small> - We're seeing positive signs that we're in the clear with this error message. However, if you're still having issues accessing Slack, please let us know at feedback@slack.com.</p><p><small>5:58pm PST</small> - We’ve seen reports of some people seeing a \\"For some reason, Slack couldn't load\\" error when accessing Slack. We’re investigating and we’ll keep you posted on any updates.</p>",
        },
      },
