          "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "<p><small>12:46pm PST</small> - Technical summaryOn December 18 at 8:55am PT we experienced an event that resulted in one of our databases being overloaded. This led to longer than usual response times for various actions in Slack, for a small subset of workspaces.Our engineering team worked on implementing a fix, and functionality was restored to all workspaces by 10:05am PT.We’re currently investigating preventive measures to ensure that this doesn’t happen again. If you’re still running into any issues, please reach out to us at feedback@slack.com.</p><p><small>10:07am PST</small> - Good news! Search and workspace management functionality is back up and running. Thank you for your patience!</p><p><small>9:59am PST</small> - We have received reports of degraded service (search, workspace management) for a subset of workspaces. We apologize for the disruption and we hope to be back to normal soon.</p><p><small>9:29am PST</small> - We’ve heard reports that some people are experiencing degraded service. Our engineers are on the case and we'll keep you posted on any updates. Thanks for your patience.</p>",
