          "value": "Incident: New users experiencing troubles with the custom Terms of Service",
        },
        "summary" => Object {
          "attrs": Map {},
          "meta": Map {
            "br" => Array [
              Object {
                "attrs": Map {},
                "meta": Map {},
                "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
              },
              Object {
                "attrs": Map {},
                "meta": Map {},
                "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
              },
            ],
          },
          "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "Technical Summary:At 10:35 AM PST on December 11, 2018, a code change was deployed that inadvertently caused users to see a “There's been a glitch…” error page instead of the Custom Terms of Service for their Enterprise Grid organization. This effectively prevented a subset of people from accessing their workspaces. After an investigation, we were able to identify and confirm the issue, and finally resolved the error at 2:15 PM PST by reverting the relevant change for all users.",
        },
        "content" => Object {
          "attrs": Map {
            "type" => "html",
          },
          "meta": Map {
            "br" => Array [
              Object {
                "attrs": Map {},
                "meta": Map {},
                "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
              },
              Object {
                "attrs": Map {},
                "meta": Map {},
                "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
              },
            ],
          },
          "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "<p><small>2:51am PST</small> - Technical Summary:At 10:35 AM PST on December 11, 2018, a code change was deployed that inadvertently caused users to see a “There's been a glitch…” error page instead of the Custom Terms of Service for their Enterprise Grid organization. This effectively prevented a subset of people from accessing their workspaces. After an investigation, we were able to identify and confirm the issue, and finally resolved the error at 2:15 PM PST by reverting the relevant change for all users.</p><p><small>2:22pm PST</small> - The custom Terms of Service should be back to normal for users once again. Thanks for sticking with us!</p><p><small>1:54pm PST</small> - Our team has isolated the issue and are actively working on a fix. We appreciate your patience.</p><p><small>1:24pm PST</small> - New users on enterprise orgs may see a \\"Glitch\\" page when trying to load the Custom \\"Terms of Service\\" page. We're looking into the cause of the issue and hope to have an update shortly.</p>",
        },
      },
      "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
      "published": "2018-12-11T13:24:48-08:00",
      "title": "Incident: New users experiencing troubles with the custom Terms of Service",
      "updated": "2018-12-12T02:51:07-08:00",
