              },
            ],
          },
          "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "<p><small>9:43pm PST</small> - Technical Summary:On December 10th, 2018 at 5:31pm PT, a workspace deletion caused a spike in our job queue as the backlog of data was cleaned up.During this period, some users may have seen delayed link unfurls. We deployed a fix at 7:41pm PT and unfurls should be working as expected going forward.We also implemented a change to job queuing to prevent this from happening again. If you experience any issues, please let us know at feedback@slack.com.</p><p><small>8:16pm PST</small> - We've been given the all-clear! Everyone should see their links preview at normal speeds now. Thank you for your patience through that.</p><p><small>8:03pm PST</small> - The team are still working to get to the bottom of these delayed link previews. Please hold tight.</p><p><small>7:34pm PST</small> - We're investigating reports of delays in previewing links. Apologies for this interruption to your day.</p>",
        },
      },
