          },
          "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "<p><small>9:03am PST</small> - Technical Summary:On November 27th at 3:07 pm PT, an update was made to the Google Drive integration that was not correctly processed. This prevented Google Calendar reminders from appearing correctly in channels for a subset of users.After an investigation of the problem, our team deployed a fix at 11:41 pm PT, where normal functionality resumed at 12:14am PT. We'll continue to monitor the integration. If you continue to experience any issues please drop us a note at feedback@slack.com.</p><p><small>12:24am PST</small> - We’ve resolved the Google Calendar issues, and all functionality should be back to normal. Sorry for the hiccup!</p><p><small>11:33pm PST</small> - We believe we've narrowed down the issue affecting our Google Calendar integration, and are close to a fix. Thanks for bearing with us!</p><p><small>11:07pm PST</small> - We're still investigating the root cause of the troubles with our Google Calendar integration, but we hope to have things fixed up shortly.</p><p><small>10:33pm PST</small> - We're currently experiencing some issues with our Google Calendar integration. We're actively investigating, and hope to have an update soon. Thanks for your patience.</p>",
        },
      },
