          "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "Technical Summary:On November 19, 2018 between 05:12 am PT and 06:00 am PT, a small percentage of our users were unable to connect to Slack.The connection issue was caused when a single Point of Presence (POP) failed to respond to requests to slack.com. Requests going through that specific POP were either delayed or timed out, which resulted in our users being unable to connect to their workspace, or experiencing slowness in Slack. We worked with our cloud provider to remove this POP from our distribution, and resolved the issue at 06:08 am.",
        },
        "content" => Object {
          "attrs": Map {
            "type" => "html",
          },
          "meta": Map {
