          "ns": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "Technical Summary:On November 7th at 12:17 AM (PT), we began experiencing issues that prevented some users in Europe from successfully connecting to their workspaces over the course of two days.These connectivity problems were caused by unexpected resource limitations in two European data centers.We have been working with our upstream service provider, AWS, to understand why this has been isolated to these two regions. In order to reduce disconnections, we have performed the following mitigation steps:• We have deployed additional hardware into the pool to distribute connections across more machines.• We have converted one of these regions to work across multiple availability zones, which was done before the beginning of Europe's workday on November 9th.• AWS has put a mitigation in place for the load balancers.We are deeply sorry for the disruption this has caused to your workdays. Please let us know if you are still experiencing any connectivity issues at feedback@slack.com.",
